83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
HOUSE AMENDMENTS TO
HOUSE BILL 4031
By COMMITTEE ON CLIMATE, ENERGY, AND ENVIRONMENT
February 11
1 On page 3 of the printed bill, delete lines 6 through 20 and insert:
2 “(B) The developer of the facility:
3 “(i) Submits, on or before December 31, 2028, a land use application to construct or operate the
4 facility to, and receives approval from, the local government within whose jurisdiction the facility
5 is proposed to be located; and
6 “(ii) Provides a written or electronic notification to the local government, and a copy of the
7 notification to the Energy Facility Siting Council, that:
8 “(I) Confirms that construction of the facility has begun such that the facility qualifies for a tax
9 credit authorized under section 45, 45Y, 48 or 48E of the Internal Revenue Code;
10 “(II) Identifies the applicant and facility;
11 “(III) Identifies the applicable federal tax credits; and
12 “(IV) Includes a brief description of actions taken to begin construction, within the meaning of
13 the applicable notices, regulations or rulings of the United States Department of the Treasury or
14 Internal Revenue Service; and
15 “(C) The facility is placed in service:
16 “(i) On or before December 31, 2030; or
17 “(ii) If the facility is placed in service after December 31, 2030, on or before a date allowed by
18 exception by the United States Department of the Treasury or Internal Revenue Service by which
19 date the facility still qualifies for a tax credit under section 45, 45Y, 48 or 48E of the Internal Re-
20 venue Code.”.
